<br>
It had been another victory for Queen Alysia as she returned to her village to remain. During the war she had a feeling that Eli had vanished. Perhaps to Utopia which he spoke of so greatly, or perhaps just away.<br>
<br>
Nevertheless, it was over. She had felt like she needed to choose between Eli and the Amazons. Alysia could never truly love a man who didnt accept her children as his own. And her main focus now was on Belle. <br>
<br>
And so, the Queen rose in through the city gates upon her white mare, the Princess riding at her side and the warriors behind them both. It had been a victory for the Amazon Nation as a Whole.<br>
<br>
She whispered words under her breath as she looked upon the ground of her lands.<br>
<br>
&quot;To a strong Amazon Nation.&quot;<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uamazonbelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AmazonBelle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#993300>(9/1/01 12:59:35 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Return from the War</span><hr size=1> Belle smiled lightly as she rode into Scynthia beside her mother. It seemed it'd been forever since she last saw the village, and it was wonderful to be home.<br>
<br>
She couldn't help but grin as she thought about the war, the defeat. She'd told everyone who'd heard about the war that the Amazons would prevail in the end... that the Amazons would always prevail, and that she had faith in her Athelfi, and they had indeed came out on top, just as she and many others expected they would.<br>
<br>
Her blue eyes shifted to Aly momentarily and she nodded her agreement to her mother's whisper.<br>
<br>
&quot;To a strong Amazon Nation.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/udawnithinia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dawnithinia </A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 319<br> <font color=#993300>(9/1/01 7:44:18 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Return from the War</span><hr size=1>  Dawn's black mare road up beside Alysia and Belle, as they came into Scynthia. The assassin gave them a strong smile.<br>
<br>
 &quot;To a strong and united Amazon Nation.&quot;<br>
<br>
 A smile formed over her lips, and her emeralds twinkled in the morning sun.<br>
<br>
 &quot;The war may have been petty, but it did something no one else had the power to do.&quot; <p>
~^*^~Dawnithinia Rivent Darkshade~^*^~
Queen of Orio-pata
