High Council Cheiftess of SoT</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Royal Fogstone</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#993300>(9/1/01 8:34:55 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Returning?...</span><hr size=1> ***Watched as his army marched back to Britannia, the war had been won. Even though there were some who were pretty badly injured, everything had turned out alright. He stood there apon a large rock hidden by the brnches of a giant willow tree... He had decided he would stay in the these lands, and also nearby lands, for old times sake.*** <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sartha>Sartha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 176<br> <font color=#993300>(9/1/01 8:43:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Return from the War</span><hr size=1> ::Sartha was at Dawn's side as well, making the passage pretty crowded. Her silvery-golden eyes were grave, but she was smiling, so they knew she was happy the war was done and over. She glanced at her Queen and Princess and nodded to them both, though she kept her voice to silence. She had been that way lately and so it was nothing new. She continued to ride Vela into the village, sitting tall upon the regal black mare:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/udelilahtragedy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Delilah Tragedy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#993300>(9/1/01 12:59:06 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Return from the War</span><hr size=1> Delilah had not returned from the war. Such a tug-of-war it was... but she didn't return with the rest of the amazons.  When the war was done, she had taken apart her tent and gathered things from the battlefields.  So many bodies... So many puddles of blood... The battlefield was nothing but a blanket of them.  Some were sliced in half through the torso, others ha been removed of their heads, others had been beaten senseless and others look beyond gruesome.  It practically broke her heart afterwards.  She had a feeling that this war could have been well prevented in the many years of the past, but couldn't quite place her fine on why.<br>
<br>
She had gathered the thing she needed and gotten on her tiger, enchanting all of her things to become feather light.  And off she went.  She was heading to Chakipolis Island, her brother Cupid's own island.  It was probably deserted and crumbling and she had an idea of what to do with that island. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ualysiaofscynthia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alysia of Scynthia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 219<br> <font color=#993300>(9/1/01 7:07:36 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Making an Announcement</span><hr size=1> Alysia dismounted her horse making her way to the center of the village where she stood before her sisters and smiled proudly.<br>
<br>
&quot;Athelfi! Sisters of Scynthia! We have once again showed that no one dares to threaten our tribe. Though death and war is never a good thing, this war has united many of us and for that I am thankful!&quot;<br>
<br>
She smiled down to Dawn and Belle.<br>
<br>
&quot;Tonight, we feast and celebrate our Victory!&quot;<br>
<br>
Cheers were heard through the tribe as the fire was lit in the center of the village and the athelfi immediatly began dancing around the flames. <br>
<br>
A few of the hunters that had stayed behind, quickly brought out meats and fruits of all variety placing them on a long table at the side of the Main Hut in the village.<br>
<br>
&quot;Amazons Unite!&quot;<br>
<br>
She cheered loudly raising her fist in the air before she stepped down and walked over to her daughter.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm going to go get ready.&quot;<br>
<br>
She smiled lightly and went off to the Queen's Hut where she was able to change out of her battle clothes and into her regular leathers. She took of the golden belt and placed it in a safe trunk where she always had it. <br>
<br>
With a few new feathered braids in her hair and a bit of ritual dancing paint on her body, she walked back out to join her sisters in the dancing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/udawnithinia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dawnithinia </A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 322<br> <font color=#993300>(9/1/01 10:05:56 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Celebration. </span><hr size=1>  Dawn sighed lightly, as she stretched abit. Before leaving her horse off at the stables, visiting her hut for a moment, to leave off a few of her weapons and then return to the center of the village to celebrate with her athelfi. This night would be more than celebrating a war that they had won, but something more special, and that was their bond. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ukalaofsmyrna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kala of Smyrna</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#993300>(9/2/01 2:50:24 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/amznkala/images/kala-01.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Erm...returning from the war....</span><hr size=1> Kala rode into the Scynthian village atop a brown steed.The black and white spotted steed she had brought with her lost it's life during the Saurian war.Go figure.<br>
<br>
She led the steed to the stables then dismounted and tied the horse off.Being dirty and having blood all over her heavy attire from the war,she goes to the bathing hut....<br>
<br>
After some moments pass,she exits the bathing hut.Nice and clean and in differ attire.Not the heavy stuff she came in with,but the change of clothing she had brought with her,her regular attire.But she wore a cloak around her shoulders and had the cloak wrapped around her nice and cozy like.Of course the clean clothes were a bit tight around her tummy,but right now it was all she had with her,and the cloak did cover the tummy well.<br>
<br>
Smelling food,she walks over to join in on the festivities.Grabbing up a plate,she piles an assortment of food on it,and walks over to a chair and sits down and eats.Yum yum. <p>|•| Kala of Smyrna |•|</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=daphnikearephiparthenia>Daphnike Arephi Parthenia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#993300>(9/2/01 8:40:33 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://mrmagoo.fortunecity.com/royo/secret/secret03.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Erm...returning from the war....</span><hr size=1> Daphnike,after bathing herself in a river and hunting a deer for the feast joins the celebration at the village.War is over, finally over and the Saurians had been defeated.Now, the Amazons could live in peace, she was hoping for long.So much blood spilled, so many deaths.She was feeling that the Great Mother protected her.She was alive and only superficially injured at her left shoulder.But many of her athelfi lost their lives and she'll never forget Alcippe's death.That war was her rite of passage.She was now a true warrior, the proud daughter of Mytilene.And a proud Amazon.<br>
<br>
Sat between the Scynthians, she raised her cup, saying:<br>
<br>
&quot;To our victory, to the Amazon Nation!And to all of you, athelfi&quot;<br>
<br>
After joining the dance, she says goodbye to her Scynthian athelfi.She was hurried to return in her homeland of Themiscrya, even if she would like to stay in the Northern Lands some more days.<br>
